                           <ab type="ruling"> The bottom line is written above the ruling.</ab>
                           
                           <ab type="pricking"> Pricks in the upper part of the folios, have
                              probably been prepared for endband stitches (s. <locus from="10" to="12">10-12</locus>)</ab>
                        </layout>
                        <layout/>
                     </layoutDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Fine and careful</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red (strong crimson)</seg>
                        Scribe: Gabra Giyorgis. The name of
                        the scribe, Gabra Giyorgis, is mentioned in the concluding supplication on
                           <locus target="#47vb">47vb</locus>. He also wrote Ms. KY-064.<date>First
                           half of 20th century</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; name of the protagonist; groups of
                           lines (alternating with black lines) on the incipit page; punctuation
                           signs (fol. 5ra) or their elements; elements of Ethiopic numerals.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">The 6th order ም (e.g., <locus target="#5ra">5ra</locus>) has a peculiar
                        shape.</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>

                     <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d1">
                        <locus target="#5r">5r</locus> (incipit page of Text I): elaborate coloured
                        (strong crimson, red) ornamental band; geometric, floral and anthropomorphic
                        motifs.</decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="e1">
                           <desc type="findingAid">- Daily readings are indicated by the names of the
                              days, incorporated into the text, in red: ዘሠሉስ: fol.18ra ዘሐሙስ: <locus target="#25va">fol. 25va</locus> ዘዓርብ: <locus target="#32ra">fol.
                                 32ra</locus> Others are written in the upper margin, in the main
                              hand, in red: ሠሉስ: <locus target="#11ra">fol. 11ra</locus> ዘረቡዕ:
                                 <locus target="#18ra">fol. 18ra</locus> ዓርብ: <locus target="#28va">fol. 28va</locus>.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e3">
                           <desc>- The word ኪሮስ is written in the upper margin, in the main hand: <locus target="#34va">fol.  34va</locus>. - Blank spaces left for the name “Kiros”: fols. 27va, 28va.</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding contemporary="true">
                        <decoNote xml:id="b1">Two wooden boards covered with reddish-brown tooled
                           leather.
 Two pairs of sewing stations.</decoNote>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="bindingMaterial">
                           <material key="wood"/>
                           <material key="leather"/>
                        </decoNote>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b3" type="Endbands"/>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b4" type="Other">Small holes are visible in the centre
                           fold of the quires, one close to the head and one close to the tail of
                           the codex.</decoNote>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b5">Blind tooled ornament on the reddish-brown leather
                           cover (at least 5 tools were used: double line fillet, triple line
                           fillet, double circle, wave form, x-form, criss-cross).</decoNote>
                     </binding>
                  </bindingDesc>
               </physDesc>
               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origPlace>
                        <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0171KY">Koholo Yoḥannǝs Dabra Betel / KY</placeName>
                     </origPlace>
                     <origDate notBefore="1850" notAfter="1900">Second half of the 19th cent. 
                        The scribe Gabra Giyorgis wrote also Ms. KY-064 which is dateable from 1881
                        to 1889 since the reigning King Yoḥannǝs and some other proper names are
                        mentioned in it.</origDate>
                  </origin>
                  <provenance>Walda Tǝnśāʾe is mentioned as the
                     commissioner on <locus target="#47ra">47ra</locus>. His name appears in the
                     supplication formulas on <locus target="#40rb">40rb</locus>, 46vb, 47va. 
                     Also, Gabra Ḥǝywat, Walatta ʾAragāwi (<locus target="#5ra">5ra</locus>, 32ra,
                     46ra, 47ra, 47vb) and Walatta Mikāʾel (<locus target="#46vb">46vb</locus>) are
                     mentioned in the supplication formulas. 
 All the names are written in
                     crimson red.</provenance>
               </history>
